WEBVTT

01:25.780 --> 01:35.030
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

01:35.590 --> 01:38.009
[Episode 8]

01:49.039 --> 01:52.570
[Parking Space]

01:59.070 --> 02:06.830
[Parking Space]

02:00.620 --> 02:01.350
Xu!

02:01.760 --> 02:02.260
Xu!

02:08.370 --> 02:10.000
What's going on?

02:12.530 --> 02:13.900
The whole Seasons Change Hostel

02:13.900 --> 02:14.860
knows about it.

02:15.360 --> 02:16.700
He's from her hometown.

02:16.900 --> 02:17.829
He's her fiancé.

02:19.180 --> 02:20.380
Don't talk nonsense.

02:20.800 --> 02:22.300
Zhuang Zhuang never said that herself.

02:22.300 --> 02:23.650
I'm not talking nonsense.

02:23.650 --> 02:25.310
He said it himself.

02:25.360 --> 02:26.840
You... Your cigarette...

02:27.960 --> 02:29.630
He brought it from Wenzhou.

02:33.500 --> 02:35.630
I haven't even opened the pack! You...

02:43.810 --> 02:44.540
You're back.

02:48.680 --> 02:49.610
Where did you go?

02:50.680 --> 02:51.960
To sell clothes.

02:52.290 --> 02:53.180
Shouldn't Zhuang Zhuang

02:53.180 --> 02:54.240
have gone with you?

02:58.300 --> 03:00.460
Didn't someone from her hometown come?

03:00.460 --> 03:02.260
What someone from her hometown?

03:03.150 --> 03:04.010
You don't know?

03:05.620 --> 03:07.310
He even shouted in the corridor

03:07.310 --> 03:09.240
that he's Zhuang Zhuang's fiancé!

03:09.530 --> 03:10.470
He told everyone.

03:10.470 --> 03:11.680
If he sees the guy

03:11.680 --> 03:13.060
in the Argentina jersey—

03:13.060 --> 03:13.930
he'll rip out

03:13.930 --> 03:15.320
your twisted guts

03:15.410 --> 03:16.870
and make a dish out of them.

03:17.300 --> 03:18.470
What kind of dish can he make?

03:18.470 --> 03:19.530
I thought about it.

03:19.590 --> 03:21.120
It can only be stewed offal.

03:21.520 --> 03:22.710
I haven't had that in a while.

03:22.710 --> 03:23.370
Let's share

03:23.370 --> 03:24.500
these twisted guts.

03:25.000 --> 03:25.600
Have some.

03:27.370 --> 03:29.370
Then... what did Zhuang Zhuang say?

03:30.150 --> 03:31.850
How would I know what she said?

03:32.650 --> 03:33.930
When her fiancé left,

03:33.930 --> 03:35.690
he gave everyone a pack of cigarettes.

03:35.690 --> 03:36.690
He asked everyone

03:36.780 --> 03:37.560
to take care

03:37.579 --> 03:39.440
of Zhuang Zhuang and such.

03:40.370 --> 03:41.970
When he got to me and Zongbao,

03:42.000 --> 03:43.300
we just ignored him.

03:43.340 --> 03:44.670
If he dares to come back,

03:44.740 --> 03:46.190
I'll rip his guts out

03:46.280 --> 03:47.540
and make stewed offal.

03:53.930 --> 03:54.560
Have some.

03:55.079 --> 03:56.480
No, thanks. You go ahead.

03:56.870 --> 03:58.520
I'm going to the restroom.

04:23.660 --> 04:24.330
Who is it?

04:29.510 --> 04:30.300
Xu.

04:31.830 --> 04:34.030
Are we still setting up the stall later?

04:35.620 --> 04:36.770
Yes.

04:37.659 --> 04:38.460
Wait a moment.

04:38.720 --> 04:39.510
I'll get changed.

04:39.510 --> 04:40.440
Okay, I'll wait.

04:57.250 --> 04:57.780
Let's go.

04:59.270 --> 05:00.480
Put the goods on the back seat.

05:00.480 --> 05:01.480
It's far away today.

05:01.480 --> 05:02.480
I'll take the bus.

05:02.750 --> 05:04.080
It's okay. I don't mind.

05:05.240 --> 05:06.040
See you later.

05:31.760 --> 05:33.020
What should I call you?

05:33.510 --> 05:34.240
Xu Shengli.

05:34.420 --> 05:35.350
Xu, spelled X-U.

05:35.360 --> 05:37.290
Shengli as in "Shengli Oilfield."

05:40.100 --> 05:41.830
I really appreciate your help.

05:41.830 --> 05:43.040
Don't mention it.

05:43.040 --> 05:44.190
Just settle in.

05:44.240 --> 05:46.010
You look pretty happy today.

05:46.480 --> 05:48.060
I'm happy for you.

05:54.120 --> 05:55.920
What's going on between you two?

05:56.070 --> 05:57.430
We're business partners.

05:57.430 --> 06:00.160
Business partners? Who are you kidding?

06:11.570 --> 06:12.390
Jerseys. Take a look.

06:12.390 --> 06:13.690
Jerseys. Argentina jerseys.

06:13.690 --> 06:15.310
-Do you want one?
-Buy two to get a discount.

06:15.310 --> 06:17.500
-Do you want an Argentina jersey?
-No, thanks.

06:17.500 --> 06:18.270
Jerseys.

06:18.420 --> 06:19.040
No, thanks.

06:19.040 --> 06:20.000
Argentina jerseys!

06:20.000 --> 06:21.130
Jerseys for sale!

06:27.570 --> 06:29.360
The game's highlights are over,

06:29.360 --> 06:31.890
but the turmoil
at the field hasn't subsided.

06:32.370 --> 06:33.250
Argentinian soccer star

06:33.250 --> 06:35.100
Maradona's drug test

06:35.100 --> 06:36.159
has been announced

06:36.240 --> 06:37.990
to be positive.

06:38.800 --> 06:40.460
Due to violation of the rules,

06:40.620 --> 06:41.740
he was suspended for 15 months

06:41.740 --> 06:44.100
by FIFA.

06:44.600 --> 06:45.510
Want a jersey?

06:45.740 --> 06:46.830
Want a jersey?

06:47.270 --> 06:48.950
Maradona has been banned.

06:48.980 --> 06:50.870
Argentina doesn't stand a chance.

06:50.870 --> 06:51.540
Not a chance.

06:51.540 --> 06:53.070
Argentina is the champion.

06:54.010 --> 06:56.270
It's Brazil that doesn't stand a chance.

07:06.870 --> 07:08.530
Argentina jerseys for sale!

07:38.010 --> 07:38.950
In the coming days,

07:38.950 --> 07:40.450
I'll visit more universities

07:40.450 --> 07:41.150
and courts.

07:41.680 --> 07:43.159
While the hype hasn't died down,

07:43.159 --> 07:44.620
I'll give it another shot.

07:45.600 --> 07:47.020
Just get some rest today.

07:47.070 --> 07:49.330
We've been trying to sell them all night.

07:49.360 --> 07:50.390
Let's take our time.

07:50.390 --> 07:51.990
We'll definitely sell them.

07:52.240 --> 07:53.070
It's my fault.

07:53.890 --> 07:55.420
I should've listened to you

07:55.510 --> 07:57.110
and stocked up on more teams.

07:59.220 --> 08:00.620
Maybe I should go now.

08:00.620 --> 08:01.750
I'll go give it a try—

08:02.360 --> 08:03.120
Enough.

08:03.600 --> 08:04.480
We made the decision

08:04.480 --> 08:05.610
together back then.

08:07.740 --> 08:08.770
They were goods from a special period.

08:08.770 --> 08:09.500
It's normal.

08:09.890 --> 08:11.550
It was a gamble from the start.

08:12.040 --> 08:13.770
We just have to accept the loss.

08:13.870 --> 08:14.400
Let's go.

08:14.540 --> 08:15.710
How can we not lose?

08:15.980 --> 08:16.870
He isn't allowed on the field.

08:16.870 --> 08:18.010
That's so frustrating.

08:18.010 --> 08:18.870
If you ask me,

08:18.890 --> 08:19.570
the others played

08:19.570 --> 08:20.570
really badly too.

08:20.800 --> 08:21.810
The others played okay.

08:21.810 --> 08:22.500
You go in first.

08:22.500 --> 08:23.230
I'm off, Bro.

08:24.830 --> 08:26.230
You're back just in time.

08:26.330 --> 08:26.740
Last night,

08:26.740 --> 08:27.750
Director Weng called

08:27.750 --> 08:29.550
and asked you to go to the office.

08:30.720 --> 08:31.930
You drank too much again?

08:31.930 --> 08:32.929
N-N-No, I didn't.

08:32.940 --> 08:33.720
Hurry up and go!

08:33.720 --> 08:34.650
Don't delay any longer!

08:34.650 --> 08:35.700
-Give him a hand.
-Hold this.

08:35.700 --> 08:36.320
I got this.

08:36.320 --> 08:36.980
Let me do it.

08:37.049 --> 08:38.710
Slow down. I've got you.

08:42.650 --> 08:43.440
Take care!

08:43.440 --> 08:43.840
Okay!

08:44.200 --> 08:44.940
Don't worry!

08:46.120 --> 08:47.360
Good lord.

08:47.510 --> 08:49.020
Are both bags full of this?

08:49.120 --> 08:49.890
Can you even sell this?

08:49.890 --> 08:52.020
They lost the game so badly yesterday.

08:52.500 --> 08:52.960
Yes.

09:19.890 --> 09:21.010
Who is it? Come in.

09:24.600 --> 09:25.460
Director Weng?

09:28.500 --> 09:29.320
Xu...

09:29.860 --> 09:30.860
Shengli, right?

09:37.300 --> 09:39.520
I finally get to see my family!

09:40.050 --> 09:40.710
Okay, okay.

09:40.910 --> 09:41.550
Okay.

09:42.030 --> 09:42.650
Okay.

09:42.940 --> 09:43.560
Come on.

09:43.860 --> 09:44.640
Come on.

09:45.240 --> 09:46.970
Help your family clean this up.

09:48.120 --> 09:48.720
My feet...

09:48.740 --> 09:49.510
are numb.

09:49.530 --> 09:53.530
["A One-man Fight"
Director: Weng Guoxing]

09:53.360 --> 09:54.910
The rumbling thunder

09:55.720 --> 09:57.230
echoed continuously.

09:57.390 --> 09:59.960
Rain poured down.

10:00.820 --> 10:01.670
Pedestrians on the street

10:01.670 --> 10:03.370
scattered like ants in a hot pan,

10:03.370 --> 10:05.350
fleeing in all directions.

10:06.000 --> 10:07.660
He walked silently in the rain

10:07.890 --> 10:09.530
as if he had lost his soul,

10:10.460 --> 10:12.450
letting the rain soak his

10:12.820 --> 10:13.470
hair,

10:13.940 --> 10:14.550
face,

10:15.250 --> 10:16.240
shoulders,

10:16.580 --> 10:18.150
a-and his shoes.

10:21.360 --> 10:22.090
Pretty good.

10:22.360 --> 10:22.900
Really?

10:23.010 --> 10:23.610
Really.

10:25.050 --> 10:26.970
If you polish this novel up,

10:27.250 --> 10:29.650
you could publish it in "Reader's Digest."

10:30.760 --> 10:33.290
You might as well
just criticize me directly.

10:34.550 --> 10:35.460
Verbose.

10:36.200 --> 10:37.230
Too verbose.

10:37.390 --> 10:38.530
Too much fluff.

10:39.320 --> 10:40.870
What you wrote is a novel,

10:40.870 --> 10:42.240
not a script.

10:42.870 --> 10:43.650
No suspense.

10:43.840 --> 10:44.570
No conflict.

10:44.630 --> 10:45.460
No twists.

10:45.740 --> 10:47.960
It lacks the kind of plot

10:47.960 --> 10:49.490
that builds anticipation.

10:49.870 --> 10:50.440
Xu.

10:51.150 --> 10:52.720
I read your script.

10:53.460 --> 10:53.990
There are

10:54.150 --> 10:55.360
some parts

10:55.440 --> 10:56.620
that show some promise.

10:56.620 --> 10:57.600
But overall,

10:57.600 --> 10:58.660
as a screenwriter,

11:00.010 --> 11:02.030
you still have a long way to go.

11:02.960 --> 11:04.500
The script is the foundation of a show.

11:04.500 --> 11:07.000
A good script is hard to come by.

11:11.030 --> 11:11.500
What?

11:12.340 --> 11:13.140
Discouraged?

11:15.390 --> 11:15.820
No.

11:17.290 --> 11:18.240
I rushed headfirst here,

11:18.240 --> 11:19.480
burning my path of return.

11:19.480 --> 11:21.480
I must fight with my back to the wall.

11:22.050 --> 11:22.910
Director Weng,

11:23.010 --> 11:24.370
just give me your feedback.

11:24.370 --> 11:24.980
I'll change it.

11:24.980 --> 11:26.040
I'll change it all.

11:30.270 --> 11:32.410
You just rushed over to Beijing like this.

11:32.410 --> 11:33.270
I also heard

11:33.270 --> 11:34.050
that you came to my studio

11:34.050 --> 11:35.530
looking for me several times.

11:35.530 --> 11:36.590
I feel bad about it.

11:37.050 --> 11:38.460
Back then, we really did

11:38.480 --> 11:39.410
have a good talk.

11:39.600 --> 11:40.170
But

11:40.910 --> 11:43.050
creating gala programs

11:43.120 --> 11:44.100
and writing movie scripts

11:44.100 --> 11:46.160
are two different things, after all.

11:50.700 --> 11:52.120
What are you doing for work now?

11:52.120 --> 11:53.720
I... I, along with a friend,

11:53.720 --> 11:54.860
opened a clothing stall.

11:54.860 --> 11:55.750
Business is not bad.

11:55.750 --> 11:57.370
It helps make ends meet.

11:58.580 --> 11:59.630
I see...

12:01.860 --> 12:02.720
How about this?

12:03.960 --> 12:04.960
As for me,

12:04.960 --> 12:06.240
I do have a project coming up

12:06.240 --> 12:07.720
that is currently in preparation.

12:07.720 --> 12:08.930
If you can manage it—

12:09.120 --> 12:09.550
I mean,

12:09.550 --> 12:10.980
if you don't have other work—

12:10.980 --> 12:11.860
I can

12:11.980 --> 12:12.820
ask my production manager

12:12.820 --> 12:14.680
to arrange for you to visit the set

12:15.150 --> 12:16.290
to experience what it's like

12:16.290 --> 12:17.120
there.

12:17.360 --> 12:19.310
It will also help you decide

12:19.620 --> 12:20.600
whether you want to

12:20.600 --> 12:21.690
dive headfirst

12:22.120 --> 12:23.420
into this industry.

12:23.860 --> 12:25.860
That would make me feel better, too.

12:26.410 --> 12:28.540
Director Weng, please don't say that.

12:28.940 --> 12:29.870
I came to Beijing,

12:29.870 --> 12:31.340
not to cling to you.

12:32.460 --> 12:33.840
But is this opportunity you mentioned

12:33.840 --> 12:34.580
f-for real?

12:34.740 --> 12:35.850
I-I'm willing.

12:36.010 --> 12:37.130
I'm absolutely willing!

12:37.130 --> 12:37.730
All right.

12:37.840 --> 12:38.980
If you're really interested,

12:38.980 --> 12:40.170
then let's count that as

12:40.170 --> 12:42.150
I'm helping to fulfill a wish of yours.

12:42.150 --> 12:42.810
How's that?

12:43.740 --> 12:44.120
I...

12:44.250 --> 12:45.910
I... Thank you, Director Weng!

12:45.910 --> 12:46.640
Thank you!

12:50.100 --> 12:51.670
[Seasons Change Hostel]

12:51.840 --> 12:53.370
Pour. Pour, pour.

12:53.750 --> 12:54.830
That's the way.

12:57.470 --> 12:59.530
It spilled! What a waste! You guys...

13:01.320 --> 13:02.340
It's amazing.

13:03.940 --> 13:04.650
Let's clink glasses.

13:04.650 --> 13:05.260
Cheers.

13:05.370 --> 13:05.820
No.

13:07.010 --> 13:08.490
What if it spills?

13:08.870 --> 13:09.670
Let's do an air toast. Come on.

13:09.670 --> 13:10.590
Air toast.

13:19.610 --> 13:20.410
Xu.

13:20.770 --> 13:22.730
What is your show about?

13:22.840 --> 13:23.750
It's a Republic era show.

13:23.750 --> 13:25.480
What kind of Republic era show?

13:25.700 --> 13:26.440
Supposedly,

13:27.750 --> 13:29.480
it's about people from all over

13:29.620 --> 13:30.670
who were displaced

13:30.670 --> 13:31.670
coming to Beiping

13:31.790 --> 13:33.320
to build a national industry,

13:33.320 --> 13:33.980
and finally

13:34.440 --> 13:35.970
made a name for themselves.

13:38.750 --> 13:39.680
Wait, isn't that

13:39.870 --> 13:40.860
talking about us?

13:40.860 --> 13:42.480
Isn't that our story?

13:43.510 --> 13:45.430
Make a name for ourselves!

13:45.480 --> 13:46.940
Make a name for ourselves!

13:47.650 --> 13:49.230
Make a name for ourselves!

13:49.270 --> 13:50.320
What are you looking at?

13:50.320 --> 13:51.580
Where are you looking?

13:53.000 --> 13:53.600
All right.

13:53.650 --> 13:54.530
Anyway,

13:54.600 --> 13:56.440
to making a name for ourselves,

13:56.550 --> 13:56.960
let's drink.

13:56.960 --> 13:57.650
Let's drink.

13:57.650 --> 13:58.400
Come on.

13:59.410 --> 14:00.050
Easy now.

14:04.790 --> 14:06.220
We wouldn't have this drink without Xu.

14:06.220 --> 14:06.840
Who is it?

14:11.890 --> 14:12.890
Really sneaky.

14:14.250 --> 14:15.250
Is everyone here?

14:17.510 --> 14:18.600
I just went looking for you,

14:18.600 --> 14:19.440
but you weren't there.

14:19.440 --> 14:20.120
Perfect timing.

14:20.120 --> 14:21.530
I have something to tell you.

14:21.530 --> 14:22.130
What is it?

14:22.360 --> 14:23.490
It's about our

14:23.630 --> 14:24.690
clothes business.

14:30.340 --> 14:31.270
Where is Ranran?

14:31.550 --> 14:32.350
Are you alone?

14:32.500 --> 14:33.510
What do you mean?

14:33.510 --> 14:34.370
Disappointed?

14:36.050 --> 14:36.550
No.

14:36.840 --> 14:37.320
Well,

14:38.030 --> 14:40.300
Xu has good news

14:40.600 --> 14:41.600
and made some dishes.

14:41.600 --> 14:42.700
We're having a gathering.

14:42.700 --> 14:43.900
Why don't you join us?

14:44.200 --> 14:45.060
J-Join us.

14:45.200 --> 14:46.250
What's the good news?

14:46.250 --> 14:47.750
Come on, Ranran. Let's eat together.

14:47.750 --> 14:48.720
No, no. Zhuang Zhuang.

14:48.720 --> 14:49.250
Zhuang Zhuang.

14:49.250 --> 14:50.530
-She's not back yet.
-Zhuang Zhuang is here.

14:50.530 --> 14:53.030
-Come on. Have a seat.
-Sit, sit.

14:53.130 --> 14:54.250
You're already drinking?

14:54.250 --> 14:55.080
What's the good news?

14:55.080 --> 14:56.000
Great news.

14:56.790 --> 14:58.440
Tell her yourself.

15:00.860 --> 15:02.790
Did the director read your script?

15:02.860 --> 15:03.540
He did.

15:03.960 --> 15:05.490
And criticized it harshly.

15:06.120 --> 15:06.900
Spit it out.

15:09.370 --> 15:10.090
Well...

15:10.770 --> 15:11.830
I'll say it for you.

15:12.370 --> 15:12.870
Well,

15:12.980 --> 15:14.860
Director Weng has given him a chance

15:14.860 --> 15:15.940
to join the crew

15:15.940 --> 15:16.670
as an intern!

15:17.170 --> 15:18.550
From now on,

15:18.630 --> 15:20.460
he'll be busy!

15:20.550 --> 15:21.750
He's going to make it.

15:21.860 --> 15:22.660
That's great.

15:23.000 --> 15:23.840
We must celebrate this.

15:23.840 --> 15:24.720
Do you have a glass?

15:24.720 --> 15:26.140
Yes, here.

15:26.200 --> 15:27.640
Then... about us...

15:28.250 --> 15:29.220
What about us?

15:30.100 --> 15:31.390
What's going on between you two?

15:31.390 --> 15:31.990
What is it?

15:32.320 --> 15:33.720
Nothing at all.

15:33.770 --> 15:34.900
-Come on.
-Nothing.

15:35.510 --> 15:36.510
What's wrong with mine?

15:36.510 --> 15:38.010
I'll pour you some.

15:38.220 --> 15:39.770
Pour some. Have some more.

15:39.770 --> 15:40.960
I'll down this one.

15:41.390 --> 15:42.650
Congratulations, Xu.

15:44.240 --> 15:45.160
Cheers.

15:45.320 --> 15:46.200
Cheers.

15:46.270 --> 15:46.970
Well...

15:47.000 --> 15:47.790
Make a name for yourself!

15:47.790 --> 15:49.190
Make a name for yourself!

15:52.960 --> 15:53.590
All right.

15:53.770 --> 15:55.290
I came here for serious business today

15:55.290 --> 15:56.150
with everyone.

15:56.200 --> 15:57.050
We can't just let

15:57.050 --> 15:58.460
what happened to Ranran slide.

15:58.460 --> 16:00.120
You should all think about it.

16:01.620 --> 16:03.290
No one is letting it slide.

16:03.620 --> 16:04.240
Besides,

16:04.240 --> 16:06.040
isn't it just about a director?

16:06.080 --> 16:07.410
If worse comes to worst,

16:08.390 --> 16:09.550
I'll go alone.

16:09.580 --> 16:10.730
I'll take him out.

16:10.870 --> 16:11.870
-That's it.
-Shut up.

16:11.870 --> 16:13.410
You got saliva all over my face.

16:13.410 --> 16:14.540
You have a big mouth.

16:14.650 --> 16:16.150
It's a hard-earned opportunity.

16:16.150 --> 16:17.100
Seize it.

16:17.170 --> 16:18.180
I'm not bluffing.

16:19.870 --> 16:21.030
-Why are you drinking without us?
-Hold up!

16:21.030 --> 16:22.120
How could you drink without us?

16:22.120 --> 16:23.240
Let's drink together.

16:23.240 --> 16:24.270
Come on. Come on.

16:25.150 --> 16:25.950
My bad.

16:25.980 --> 16:26.410
Right.

16:34.050 --> 16:35.270
You guys look pretty sharp

16:35.270 --> 16:36.340
in these jerseys.

16:36.530 --> 16:37.460
Xu

16:37.600 --> 16:38.800
bought so many of them

16:38.940 --> 16:39.860
and couldn't sell them.

16:39.860 --> 16:41.650
-We got them cheap.
-Don't drink too much.

16:41.650 --> 16:42.050
Right?

16:42.130 --> 16:42.690
You never learn.

16:42.690 --> 16:44.340
Everyone's wearing this

16:44.370 --> 16:45.870
in this hallway.

16:46.050 --> 16:47.000
They're all number 10—

16:47.000 --> 16:47.630
Maradona.

16:48.260 --> 16:49.860
A hallway full of Maradonas.

16:51.240 --> 16:52.300
Have some food.

16:53.250 --> 16:54.910
She doesn't have chopsticks.

16:55.000 --> 16:55.600
Come on, eat.

16:55.600 --> 16:57.110
Dig in.

16:57.390 --> 16:58.150
Eat something.

16:58.150 --> 16:58.610
Thanks.

16:58.740 --> 17:00.670
Drinking manners show character.

17:02.000 --> 17:03.130
We still need to find a way

17:03.130 --> 17:04.190
to help Ranran.

17:06.849 --> 17:07.839
In this room,

17:09.950 --> 17:11.319
Xu is the smartest.

17:12.569 --> 17:14.440
Help us think of a way.

17:14.440 --> 17:16.460
I've been thinking about it.

17:17.349 --> 17:18.210
How about this?

17:18.510 --> 17:20.140
Go back and tell Ranran

17:20.790 --> 17:22.099
to eat well

17:22.329 --> 17:23.190
and sleep well.

17:23.740 --> 17:25.430
Leave this to us.

17:28.500 --> 17:30.700
Give Cao Ye's painting to the director?

17:32.030 --> 17:32.900
Cao Ye's painting

17:32.900 --> 17:34.230
is pretty presentable.

17:36.660 --> 17:38.550
But who is Director Ma?

17:38.590 --> 17:39.810
He can tell real Maotai from fake

17:39.810 --> 17:41.060
just by tasting it.

17:41.700 --> 17:42.590
As for that painting,

17:42.590 --> 17:43.310
he'll definitely know its quality

17:43.310 --> 17:44.890
just by looking at it.

17:46.250 --> 17:48.560
Cao Ye's paintings are good.

17:49.160 --> 17:49.560
But...

17:49.830 --> 17:51.290
But he's a nobody.

17:51.740 --> 17:53.550
I'm afraid
the director won't appreciate it.

17:53.550 --> 17:54.280
That's true.

17:56.900 --> 17:58.300
But at this point of time,

17:58.680 --> 18:00.010
we have nothing to lose.

18:00.920 --> 18:02.520
The most important thing now

18:02.530 --> 18:04.190
is for you to meet Director Ma.

18:07.000 --> 18:07.440
Okay.

18:07.770 --> 18:10.110
-Take this.
-Just one word:

18:12.700 --> 18:13.140
bluff!

18:14.290 --> 18:15.570
Bluff about how good your painting is,

18:15.570 --> 18:16.570
and this thing...

18:17.350 --> 18:18.410
would be in the bag.

18:19.980 --> 18:21.710
Bluff, not blow!

18:23.070 --> 18:25.220
I really don't understand your industry.

18:25.220 --> 18:26.720
I can't join.

18:26.980 --> 18:28.900
Besides, I'm always about

18:28.940 --> 18:30.200
real talent and learning.

18:30.200 --> 18:31.610
I don't know how to bluff.

18:32.740 --> 18:34.070
Cao, you...

18:36.110 --> 18:38.510
Usually
when we don't let you do something,

18:38.900 --> 18:40.250
you try so hard to rush forward.

18:40.250 --> 18:41.830
Now that we're letting you go,

18:41.830 --> 18:43.140
you're chickening out.

18:43.140 --> 18:43.740
It's fine.

18:44.680 --> 18:45.350
I'll go.

18:45.750 --> 18:46.700
Like hell you will.

18:46.700 --> 18:48.000
You can't even play the saxophone well.

18:48.000 --> 18:49.220
D-Do you know anything about painting?

18:49.220 --> 18:50.330
What if they find out?

18:50.330 --> 18:51.400
They won't.

18:51.400 --> 18:52.460
There are so many people in the country.

18:52.460 --> 18:53.000
How will they find out?

18:53.000 --> 18:54.060
But what if they do?

18:54.440 --> 18:55.050
Impossible.

18:55.050 --> 18:56.160
If they find out, who's responsible?

18:56.160 --> 18:57.070
It's okay.

18:57.350 --> 18:58.550
Let me say a few words.

18:59.270 --> 19:00.800
If it doesn't work, I'll go.

19:02.000 --> 19:02.530
Zongbao.

19:02.610 --> 19:04.620
Your accent doesn't sound right.

19:04.740 --> 19:06.720
Can't a painter be from He'nan?

19:06.830 --> 19:07.480
Sure, I guess.

19:07.480 --> 19:07.810
Sure.

19:08.460 --> 19:09.160
But you don't have

19:09.160 --> 19:10.560
this artistic long hair.

19:10.640 --> 19:12.400
Picasso was bald.

19:12.460 --> 19:13.720
Picasso?

19:13.750 --> 19:14.750
Let... Let me

19:14.750 --> 19:15.750
shave your head then.

19:15.750 --> 19:16.330
No way!

19:16.330 --> 19:17.830
I don't want to take on
Qing dynasty costume drama roles.

19:17.830 --> 19:18.750
Zongbao.

19:18.830 --> 19:20.070
Did you forget how you

19:20.160 --> 19:21.310
got busted last time?

19:21.310 --> 19:22.710
That was because I drank.

19:22.770 --> 19:23.160
I—

19:23.160 --> 19:23.890
Listen to me.

19:25.570 --> 19:27.050
It's better for Liangliang to go.

19:27.050 --> 19:27.480
Why?

19:29.060 --> 19:30.450
He knows how to bluff.

19:33.190 --> 19:34.600
More like blow the saxophone.

19:34.600 --> 19:36.820
Not just the saxophone.

19:37.830 --> 19:39.110
But having said that,

19:39.680 --> 19:41.030
Ranran

19:41.090 --> 19:42.260
is unable to hide

19:42.420 --> 19:43.530
her emotions.

19:43.770 --> 19:45.420
It's written all over her face.

19:45.420 --> 19:46.820
That's hard to overcome.

19:47.310 --> 19:47.770
Well...

19:47.880 --> 19:49.480
Th-That's just in real life.

19:50.140 --> 19:51.460
You just tell her

19:51.530 --> 19:52.910
to treat it like acting.

19:54.640 --> 19:57.050
Shen is actually a good actress.

19:57.740 --> 19:58.330
Anyway,

19:59.570 --> 20:01.430
weaving baskets involves skill,

20:02.530 --> 20:04.260
but the finish is what matters.

20:05.290 --> 20:06.090
You should...

20:08.380 --> 20:09.900
put in effort for this painting.

20:09.900 --> 20:10.460
Right.

20:10.570 --> 20:11.720
What are you talking about?

20:11.720 --> 20:12.510
What do you mean?

20:12.510 --> 20:14.370
I put effort into every painting.

20:15.050 --> 20:16.770
If that director

20:17.160 --> 20:18.510
doesn't like my painting,

20:18.510 --> 20:20.570
it's because his taste is flawed!

20:22.480 --> 20:23.340
Listen to me.

20:23.510 --> 20:25.770
You must read my poem

20:25.770 --> 20:26.770
to that director.

20:27.220 --> 20:27.880
Which poem?

20:28.030 --> 20:30.970
A golden fish was never meant to
stay in a pond;

20:32.430 --> 20:35.630
When wind and clouds arise,
it shall become a dragon!

20:36.310 --> 20:38.970
When the day comes that I,
Cao Ye, make my name,

20:39.940 --> 20:42.990
my paintings would be worth a fortune!

20:51.190 --> 20:51.800
Come in.

20:54.220 --> 20:54.940
Director Ma.

20:54.940 --> 20:57.670
-Hello, Director.
-Sorry for wasting your time.

20:57.770 --> 20:58.920
I'm sorry.

20:59.850 --> 21:01.460
I'm not some big shot.

21:01.460 --> 21:03.120
I'm just an ordinary citizen.

21:03.220 --> 21:04.550
Taking up a bit of my time

21:05.610 --> 21:07.740
won't cause an international affair.

21:07.820 --> 21:10.680
Stop pulling my leg.
You're generous, Director Ma.

21:11.940 --> 21:12.670
Director Ma.

21:13.380 --> 21:14.290
I came here

21:14.310 --> 21:16.460
specifically to apologize to you.

21:16.960 --> 21:19.620
I'm really sorry
about what happened last time.

21:23.530 --> 21:24.130
It's okay.

21:24.790 --> 21:26.050
Don't take it to heart.

21:26.090 --> 21:29.380
[Character settings]

21:27.880 --> 21:29.940
Xiao Cui explained everything to me.

21:30.850 --> 21:34.020
You were deceived too.

21:35.420 --> 21:36.620
Thank you, Director.

21:39.480 --> 21:40.030
What?

21:41.440 --> 21:43.220
Getting emotional already?

21:45.790 --> 21:47.450
Just be careful in the future.

21:48.220 --> 21:48.700
Go back.

21:49.740 --> 21:50.280
Director,

21:50.280 --> 21:51.070
I came here

21:51.070 --> 21:52.690
with a painting

21:52.770 --> 21:53.640
for you.

21:53.680 --> 21:55.190
S-See if you like it.

22:03.570 --> 22:05.120
This is painted quite well.

22:06.940 --> 22:08.830
[Character settings]

22:08.000 --> 22:08.800
Who drew this?

22:09.770 --> 22:11.630
-This painting...
-I painted it.

22:12.750 --> 22:15.060
I've studied painting since childhood.

22:15.360 --> 22:19.190
I studied
under a famous master in the country,

22:19.550 --> 22:20.360
Mr. Cao—

22:21.610 --> 22:22.640
I can't quite

22:22.700 --> 22:23.780
reveal his name.

22:24.050 --> 22:25.250
But our works

22:25.250 --> 22:27.330
have been exhibited
both domestically and abroad.

22:27.330 --> 22:29.460
I've made a name for myself in the city.

22:30.050 --> 22:31.380
My future is definitely

22:32.090 --> 22:32.770
boundless.

22:34.030 --> 22:35.160
Your future?

22:36.860 --> 22:37.530
Director Ma,

22:37.530 --> 22:38.460
what he means is,

22:38.530 --> 22:39.720
in the art industry

22:39.720 --> 22:40.920
one can

22:41.000 --> 22:41.800
become famous

22:42.010 --> 22:43.620
overnight, out of nowhere.

22:43.760 --> 22:44.720
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

22:44.720 --> 22:45.980
The way Mr. Cui puts it

22:45.980 --> 22:46.850
is quite accurate.

22:46.850 --> 22:47.740
That's just how it is.

22:47.740 --> 22:48.140
Right.

22:49.920 --> 22:51.070
But this kind of style

22:50.020 --> 22:51.660
[Character settings]

22:52.900 --> 22:53.880
isn't really my thing.

22:53.880 --> 22:55.500
Then what kind of style do you prefer?

22:55.500 --> 22:56.670
I like portraits.

22:57.750 --> 22:58.580
Portraits?

22:58.660 --> 22:59.110
Yeah.

23:00.480 --> 23:01.030
Look.

23:01.440 --> 23:04.180
Could you draw a sketch for me?

23:25.530 --> 23:26.190
Don't move.

23:27.570 --> 23:28.680
Did you ask whose noodles these are?

23:28.680 --> 23:29.660
You just start eating?

23:29.660 --> 23:30.830
Well, they're right here in front of me.

23:30.830 --> 23:31.940
It'd be a waste not to...

23:31.940 --> 23:34.400
Just because they're there
doesn't mean you can eat them.

23:34.400 --> 23:35.310
I did you a huge favor!

23:35.310 --> 23:36.220
Can't I at least get a bowl of noodles?

23:36.220 --> 23:37.090
What exactly did you help me with?

23:37.090 --> 23:37.480
Fine!

23:38.310 --> 23:38.850
Alright!

23:39.330 --> 23:40.270
From now on,

23:40.270 --> 23:41.610
Ranran is my little sister,

23:41.610 --> 23:43.470
and she has nothing to do with you.

23:47.530 --> 23:48.590
Hold on, what's...

23:49.830 --> 23:51.290
What's with the long face?

23:52.270 --> 23:54.070
You didn't handle that director?

23:54.070 --> 23:54.700
Get lost.

23:56.180 --> 23:57.110
You didn't hype it up enough?

23:57.110 --> 23:58.310
I blew my cover, okay?

23:58.900 --> 24:00.270
He doesn't even know Cao Ye.

24:00.270 --> 24:01.480
How could you possibly get exposed?

24:01.480 --> 24:02.740
I panicked at that time,

24:02.740 --> 24:04.740
so I said I was the one who painted it.

24:04.960 --> 24:07.670
Even if you did paint it,

24:07.980 --> 24:09.610
so what? He didn't believe you?

24:09.610 --> 24:10.160
Shh.

24:11.740 --> 24:12.270
Look.

24:13.010 --> 24:15.980
Could you draw a sketch for me?

24:17.770 --> 24:19.110
Sure. No problem.

24:19.570 --> 24:20.660
But... I...

24:20.940 --> 24:22.160
I hope you

24:22.160 --> 24:23.130
don't mind me asking.

24:23.130 --> 24:23.750
Could you

24:24.090 --> 24:25.630
give me a photo of yourself?

24:25.940 --> 24:26.920
I'll go back,

24:27.960 --> 24:29.960
draw it properly, and give it to you.

24:30.110 --> 24:31.370
Why do you need a photo?

24:31.590 --> 24:32.400
I'm standing

24:32.400 --> 24:33.460
right here, right?

24:33.660 --> 24:34.120
And now

24:34.500 --> 24:35.830
we've got a pencil here.

24:36.380 --> 24:36.970
Cui.

24:37.240 --> 24:38.960
Get him a piece of sketch paper.

24:38.960 --> 24:39.610
O-okay.

24:39.790 --> 24:40.320
Perfect.

24:42.220 --> 24:43.480
What's wrong with you?

24:44.110 --> 24:44.860
Well,

24:45.350 --> 24:46.280
take a look at me.

24:47.220 --> 24:48.960
Is this pose okay?

24:49.030 --> 24:50.380
It's okay. No problem.

24:50.590 --> 24:51.070
Come here.

24:51.070 --> 24:52.510
It's rare for Director Ma
to be in such a good mood.

24:52.510 --> 24:54.110
Hurry and draw his portrait.

24:54.200 --> 24:55.340
Sure. No problem.

24:55.700 --> 24:56.180
Director, well...

24:56.180 --> 24:57.500
I need to use the restroom first.

24:57.500 --> 24:58.500
I... I need to use the restroom.

24:58.500 --> 24:59.910
My stomach's upset.

25:00.220 --> 25:01.140
The restroom is right there.

25:01.140 --> 25:01.810
It's right over there.

25:01.810 --> 25:03.380
-No, it's not good to use the one in your room.
-I can wait. I can wait.

25:03.380 --> 25:04.510
No, no, no. I'll just...

25:04.510 --> 25:05.310
Get back here!

25:05.340 --> 25:10.060
["I Am An Outlander" Production Crew]

25:12.290 --> 25:13.500
What's going on?

25:17.160 --> 25:18.040
Director Ma.

25:19.700 --> 25:21.230
First it's the fake liquor,

25:22.290 --> 25:23.480
then a fake artist.

25:26.110 --> 25:26.660
Is anything even real

25:26.660 --> 25:27.850
in this world?

25:34.830 --> 25:35.430
It's over.

25:36.030 --> 25:36.550
It's game over!

25:36.550 --> 25:37.410
It's game over!

25:38.070 --> 25:39.670
You can't do anything right.

25:39.850 --> 25:41.750
What do you mean I can't do anything right?

25:41.750 --> 25:43.250
You bragged all the way there,

25:43.250 --> 25:44.090
and the hype was already set,

25:44.090 --> 25:45.160
so I had to play along with you, didn't I?

25:45.160 --> 25:46.590
Then what impression

25:46.590 --> 25:47.550
did Ranran leave on that director?

25:47.550 --> 25:48.350
What impression?

25:48.350 --> 25:49.350
You tell me!

25:49.350 --> 25:50.810
It's all thanks to you!

25:50.880 --> 25:52.010
Fine, fine!

25:52.550 --> 25:53.350
It's my fault.

25:53.850 --> 25:55.910
I shouldn't have given her that idea.

25:56.330 --> 25:57.130
Alright then.

25:58.200 --> 25:59.640
I'll go find Director Ma,

25:59.660 --> 26:00.500
and explain the whole thing

26:00.500 --> 26:02.220
to him in full detail.

26:11.380 --> 26:12.440
What are you doing?

26:14.180 --> 26:14.530
What?

26:15.440 --> 26:17.370
Do I need to apologize to you first?

26:17.920 --> 26:19.810
It's not that.

26:20.270 --> 26:21.430
I want to thank you.

26:22.460 --> 26:23.060
Thank you.

26:35.310 --> 26:36.450
It actually worked!

26:39.830 --> 26:41.150
Get out, both of you.

26:41.240 --> 26:42.140
I'm really sorry.

26:42.140 --> 26:43.160
Move! Move it!

26:42.210 --> 26:45.560
[Prop Vehicle] [Prop ID]

26:43.160 --> 26:43.620
Hold on.

26:43.680 --> 26:44.770
Mr. Cui, Mr. Cui, listen.

26:44.770 --> 26:45.380
Don't call me that.

26:45.380 --> 26:46.010
Mr. Cui,

26:46.010 --> 26:47.010
please give us one more chance.

26:47.010 --> 26:47.590
Director.

26:47.590 --> 26:48.320
Director Ma,

26:48.880 --> 26:50.110
I know that I upset you

26:50.110 --> 26:51.350
because of that fake liquor thing.

26:51.350 --> 26:52.250
After I went back,

26:52.250 --> 26:53.500
I felt terrible about it.

26:53.500 --> 26:54.810
Because I was afraid of offending you,

26:54.810 --> 26:55.660
and losing this

26:55.660 --> 26:57.060
rare opportunity to act.

26:57.270 --> 26:58.530
I couldn't afford anything expensive

26:58.530 --> 26:59.590
to make it up to you.

27:00.010 --> 27:01.480
So my friends at the hostel

27:01.570 --> 27:03.170
came up with this idea for me.

27:03.460 --> 27:04.290
I never expected

27:04.290 --> 27:05.070
that things would

27:05.070 --> 27:06.070
go this far.

27:06.660 --> 27:08.220
No matter what, it's my fault.

27:08.220 --> 27:10.220
Director Ma, I'm sorry.

27:10.920 --> 27:12.610
Director, don't blame Ranran for this.

27:11.580 --> 27:14.120
[Prop Vehicle] [Prop ID]

27:12.640 --> 27:13.900
If anyone's to blame, it's me.

27:13.900 --> 27:15.430
I acted on my own.

27:15.500 --> 27:17.220
Director, Ranran came to Beijing

27:17.220 --> 27:18.180
to pursue her dream

27:18.180 --> 27:20.040
of becoming an actress.

27:20.530 --> 27:21.750
I don't want her to miss this chance

27:21.750 --> 27:22.880
because of me.

27:23.330 --> 27:24.270
I apologize to you.

27:24.270 --> 27:24.870
I'm sorry.

27:27.070 --> 27:28.180
Director, how about this?

27:28.180 --> 27:28.710
If you...

27:28.770 --> 27:30.150
Enough. Stop talking.

27:31.160 --> 27:31.750
If you still

27:31.750 --> 27:32.470
feel bad about it,

27:32.470 --> 27:33.380
then just hit me and get it over with.

27:32.590 --> 27:36.290
[Prop Vehicle] [Prop ID]

27:33.420 --> 27:34.160
Let's go.

27:34.200 --> 27:35.000
Wait a minute.

27:35.160 --> 27:36.050
It's my fault. It's on me.

27:36.050 --> 27:36.420
Let's go.

27:36.420 --> 27:37.220
Hold on. Wait.

27:38.770 --> 27:39.370
Come here.

27:40.700 --> 27:42.300
Take this painting with you.

27:54.880 --> 27:56.720
To be honest,

27:59.550 --> 28:01.210
this painting is really good.

28:02.500 --> 28:03.400
Shen Ranran,

28:04.070 --> 28:05.440
you're pretty,

28:06.790 --> 28:08.650
and you're also very articulate.

28:10.500 --> 28:12.290
But why not focus your energy

28:12.850 --> 28:15.030
on the audition instead?

28:17.680 --> 28:19.140
If the audition goes well,

28:19.240 --> 28:20.770
when the movie is released,

28:21.510 --> 28:22.770
you can invite your friends

28:22.770 --> 28:24.500
to drink that liquor together.

28:27.600 --> 28:28.930
Thank you, Director Ma.

28:31.870 --> 28:32.560
Director,

28:32.740 --> 28:34.400
I can also play the saxophone.

28:34.700 --> 28:36.220
I know you can.

28:37.050 --> 28:37.680
Director, listen.

28:37.680 --> 28:38.800
I really mean it.

28:38.850 --> 28:39.680
Just stop talking.

28:39.680 --> 28:40.250
Okay?

28:40.250 --> 28:41.110
I...

28:41.850 --> 28:43.710
Director Ma has forgiven you two.

28:44.030 --> 28:45.230
Thank you, Director.

28:45.480 --> 28:46.370
Shen Ranran.

28:48.330 --> 28:49.730
Go back and prepare well.

28:53.420 --> 28:54.250
That's so interesting.

28:54.250 --> 28:54.990
It worked!

28:55.940 --> 28:57.180
Try it. Is it good?

28:58.530 --> 28:59.390
It's just okay.

28:59.920 --> 29:00.590
You haven't even tasted it yet.

29:00.590 --> 29:01.140
How can you say it's just okay?

29:01.140 --> 29:02.250
It looks average to me.

29:02.250 --> 29:04.380
My mom made this sauce this afternoon.

29:04.400 --> 29:05.790
The noodles are handmade.

29:05.790 --> 29:06.660
Try it and tell me what you think.

29:06.660 --> 29:07.880
A bite of noodles first, then a bite of garlic.

29:07.880 --> 29:09.940
I know. You don't have to tell me that.

29:10.720 --> 29:11.350
Xu,

29:11.590 --> 29:13.200
I really have to thank you

29:14.090 --> 29:15.570
for what you did for me and Ranran.

29:15.570 --> 29:16.530
Without your help,

29:16.530 --> 29:17.680
this wouldn't have happened.

29:17.680 --> 29:18.240
You have no idea

29:18.240 --> 29:19.590
how happy Ranran was

29:20.380 --> 29:21.740
this afternoon.

29:21.790 --> 29:22.590
Let me tell you this.

29:22.590 --> 29:23.720
I'm just as happy

29:23.720 --> 29:25.230
as she is.

29:25.700 --> 29:26.790
Seeing her like that,

29:26.790 --> 29:27.330
I just...

29:27.330 --> 29:28.920
I don't even know how to describe it.

29:28.920 --> 29:29.900
But anyway,

29:29.960 --> 29:31.240
you and Zhuang Zhuang

29:31.480 --> 29:33.940
lost a lot of money on that clothing business.

29:33.940 --> 29:35.500
Don't keep it bottled up.

29:35.620 --> 29:37.660
If you're short on cash, just tell me.

29:37.660 --> 29:38.310
And if

29:38.460 --> 29:39.400
I have some money,

29:39.400 --> 29:40.110
I'll lend you some.

29:40.110 --> 29:40.710
If I don't,

29:40.740 --> 29:41.770
I can borrow some

29:41.770 --> 29:43.030
-from my mom.
-No need.

29:43.750 --> 29:44.880
I know you're embarrassed

29:44.880 --> 29:45.750
to ask me for money.

29:45.750 --> 29:47.250
But you have to think about it.

29:47.250 --> 29:48.940
What's your plan for that business

29:48.940 --> 29:50.070
with Zhuang Zhuang?

29:55.090 --> 29:56.610
I haven't discussed it with her yet.

29:56.610 --> 29:57.670
Then find a chance.

29:58.810 --> 29:59.830
You have to

29:59.830 --> 30:01.090
make your own chance!

30:01.140 --> 30:02.500
Earlier, when I was on the rooftop,

30:02.500 --> 30:03.000
I saw her carrying

30:03.000 --> 30:04.550
this huge basket of laundry.

30:04.550 --> 30:05.790
So many clothes, so heavy—

30:05.790 --> 30:07.420
and she was hanging them up one by one,

30:07.420 --> 30:08.550
all by herself.

30:08.550 --> 30:09.900
Isn't that a perfect chance?

30:09.900 --> 30:10.310
You...

30:12.180 --> 30:12.960
you have to do something

30:12.960 --> 30:14.420
to spark things up, right?

30:15.530 --> 30:16.860
This kid is so clueless.

30:23.550 --> 30:25.090
You're washing the sheets again

30:25.090 --> 30:26.700
without even asking me to help?

30:26.700 --> 30:28.700
Why do I need to bother you with this?

30:33.710 --> 30:34.570
Do it like this.

30:41.940 --> 30:43.000
Congratulations.

30:43.110 --> 30:44.840
You finally get to make a movie.

30:48.140 --> 30:49.220
Is it the script

30:49.250 --> 30:50.380
you sent out before?

30:52.110 --> 30:53.810
Mine is still a long way off.

30:55.070 --> 30:56.140
It's Director Weng.

30:56.140 --> 30:58.060
He has a project starting soon,

30:58.420 --> 30:59.640
and he said I could join the crew

30:59.640 --> 31:00.700
to learn the ropes.

31:03.680 --> 31:05.160
I don't really know much about that stuff.

31:05.160 --> 31:06.870
Anyway, it's all good news.

31:09.790 --> 31:11.320
I... I've thought about it.

31:11.900 --> 31:13.450
Once I join the crew,

31:13.770 --> 31:15.500
I'll work there during the day,

31:15.700 --> 31:17.230
and still stock up at night.

31:17.550 --> 31:18.530
I'll get up early in the morning

31:18.530 --> 31:19.960
to deliver the goods over.

31:19.960 --> 31:21.030
The shoot only lasts two months.

31:21.030 --> 31:21.720
After that,

31:21.740 --> 31:23.400
we can continue our business.

31:23.960 --> 31:25.310
Don't worry about it.

31:26.610 --> 31:27.160
Lately,

31:27.160 --> 31:29.050
Mr. Zheng asked me to prepare for the exam.

31:29.050 --> 31:30.610
I might need to take extra classes.

31:30.610 --> 31:31.850
So I was thinking,

31:32.790 --> 31:34.990
maybe we should close the stall for now.

31:35.290 --> 31:36.380
But don't worry.

31:36.720 --> 31:38.030
I've talked to Yan.

31:38.160 --> 31:40.050
She'll help sell the clothes for us,

31:40.050 --> 31:40.960
and I'll give her a cut

31:40.960 --> 31:41.760
from my share.

31:44.250 --> 31:45.400
Does "closing the stall"

31:45.400 --> 31:46.600
mean permanently?

31:49.290 --> 31:50.490
Don't worry about it.

31:51.220 --> 31:52.140
Anyway, from the very start,

31:52.140 --> 31:53.940
I was the one who wanted to sell clothes.

31:53.940 --> 31:54.900
You just happened to have time,

31:54.900 --> 31:56.500
so we teamed up temporarily.

31:56.680 --> 31:58.740
We're bound to part ways eventually.

32:39.030 --> 32:39.550
So...

32:41.050 --> 32:43.020
after you join the crew,

32:44.180 --> 32:45.580
will you still live here?

32:46.740 --> 32:47.540
I guess so.

32:50.250 --> 32:52.750
But I heard that for crews,

32:53.510 --> 32:55.510
people should live together on set.

33:00.140 --> 33:00.870
That's good.

33:05.420 --> 33:07.380
Aren't you afraid Little Northeasterner

33:07.380 --> 33:08.900
will rent out your bed to someone else?

33:08.900 --> 33:10.200
He definitely will.

33:11.980 --> 33:13.160
And the new tenant

33:13.250 --> 33:14.440
will have to face those three's

33:14.440 --> 33:15.550
endless tests.

33:28.290 --> 33:30.090
-Eat well.
-You need to eat well.

33:43.030 --> 33:43.420
Okay.

34:15.500 --> 34:15.960
Zhuang.

34:16.210 --> 34:17.300
The outfit you picked for me

34:17.300 --> 34:18.360
looks really good.

34:19.070 --> 34:21.199
I think it's still missing something.

34:21.980 --> 34:22.360
Come here.

34:22.360 --> 34:22.730
I...

34:23.800 --> 34:25.600
I think it's good enough, right?

34:26.650 --> 34:27.909
Take a look at this one.

34:27.920 --> 34:29.380
This one is a bit brighter.

34:30.460 --> 34:30.940
Zhuang.

34:30.940 --> 34:32.110
I think the one I'm wearing

34:32.110 --> 34:33.530
is pretty enough.

34:33.570 --> 34:35.420
There are so many people auditioning.

34:35.420 --> 34:36.130
You need to leave a strong impression

34:36.130 --> 34:37.060
on the director.

34:37.130 --> 34:38.929
Isn't it enough just to act well?

34:38.940 --> 34:40.340
Let's just raise the bar.

34:40.980 --> 34:42.620
You really are a big sister to me.

34:42.620 --> 34:43.370
Hurry up.

34:52.340 --> 34:53.260
Let's speed it up, guys!

34:53.260 --> 34:53.840
Coming through. Coming through.

34:53.840 --> 34:54.840
Hurry up.

34:55.650 --> 34:56.570
Make way, please.

34:56.570 --> 34:57.840
Come here, extras ove there.

34:57.840 --> 34:59.540
Come over here.

34:59.980 --> 35:01.170
Time to go over the scene. Come on.

35:01.170 --> 35:02.400
Listen up, everyone.

35:02.690 --> 35:04.550
Today's scene is very important.

35:04.730 --> 35:06.570
Once you're on set,

35:06.610 --> 35:08.230
you have to follow the director's lead.

35:08.230 --> 35:10.030
Don't look so dull and lifeless.

35:10.030 --> 35:10.960
Get energized!

35:11.340 --> 35:12.880
The sooner we finish, the sooner we wrap.

35:12.880 --> 35:13.510
Hello, Director.

35:13.510 --> 35:14.710
Why aren't you in costume yet?

35:14.710 --> 35:15.980
No, no, no. I'm a screenwriter.

35:15.980 --> 35:16.660
I'm looking for Director Weng.

35:16.660 --> 35:19.260
Director Weng isn't here. He's by the monitor.

35:20.690 --> 35:21.920
Can you do this or not?

35:22.480 --> 35:23.150
Don't think just because we started filming,

35:23.150 --> 35:25.080
you've already earned your money.

35:25.130 --> 35:25.660
Alright.

35:26.320 --> 35:26.720
Right.

35:26.820 --> 35:28.150
Later, we'll lay down the track.

35:28.150 --> 35:29.340
Lay down the whole track here.

35:29.340 --> 35:30.010
You two,

35:30.010 --> 35:31.190
-go rehearse together.
-Okay. I'll run through it with him again.

35:31.190 --> 35:31.900
Yeah, rehearse the scene.

35:31.900 --> 35:32.520
Rehearse.

35:49.000 --> 35:49.500
Come on.

35:50.550 --> 35:51.480
You and that guy—

35:51.610 --> 35:52.870
go fix that over there.

35:53.510 --> 35:54.400
Xu Shengli!

35:55.820 --> 35:56.190
Here.

35:59.190 --> 35:59.600
Okay.

35:59.690 --> 36:00.380
Got it.

36:01.800 --> 36:04.800
Repairing range hoods!

36:04.800 --> 36:06.960
Unclogging drains!

36:07.060 --> 36:14.430
[Mingyue Audio & Video Shop]

36:09.820 --> 36:12.440
Repairing range hoods!

36:12.440 --> 36:13.280
Plumber!

36:14.630 --> 36:15.760
My drain is clogged.

36:15.830 --> 36:17.380
-Can you give it a poke to clear it?
-Coming.

36:17.380 --> 36:20.320
Hang on. Let me turn around.

36:21.260 --> 36:22.180
Right here?

36:22.760 --> 36:24.050
Come and take a look.

36:25.220 --> 36:29.720
[Mingyue Audio & Video Shop]

36:26.230 --> 36:27.180
Okay, let me see.

36:27.260 --> 36:28.260
Come take a look.

36:28.840 --> 36:29.640
What's wrong?

36:37.210 --> 36:37.690
Cut.

36:40.590 --> 36:41.050
Li Li.

36:42.170 --> 36:42.770
Thank you.

36:43.900 --> 36:45.100
Thank you, Director.

36:51.680 --> 36:52.460
Shen Ranran.

36:54.110 --> 36:54.570
Coming.

36:55.510 --> 36:57.580
I think we should reconsider.

37:01.690 --> 37:02.420
Director Ma.

37:03.020 --> 37:03.880
Ranran's here.

37:05.230 --> 37:06.360
Hello, Director Ma.

37:26.030 --> 37:26.650
You...

37:27.610 --> 37:29.510
Your outfit...

37:30.420 --> 37:30.860
Director,

37:30.860 --> 37:32.360
are you saying her outfit isn't..

37:32.360 --> 37:33.570
No, no. W-What?

37:33.590 --> 37:34.510
Keep quiet.

37:36.570 --> 37:37.170
Well...

37:37.900 --> 37:39.570
Will you do a turn?

37:40.070 --> 37:40.460
Okay.

37:45.380 --> 37:47.550
The way you styled this outfit

37:50.890 --> 37:53.960
fits the style of the era,

37:55.110 --> 37:57.110
and shows a strong character trait.

37:59.230 --> 38:00.000
Well,

38:00.360 --> 38:01.890
you have a good taste.

38:02.110 --> 38:03.130
Thank you, Director.

38:03.130 --> 38:04.130
I read the script.

38:04.190 --> 38:05.800
Although it's just a segment,

38:05.800 --> 38:07.130
I feel that this outfit

38:07.190 --> 38:08.650
suits the character best.

38:13.300 --> 38:14.360
For an actor,

38:14.730 --> 38:16.860
let's put acting skills aside for now.

38:17.010 --> 38:19.010
One must have a sense of aesthetics.

38:19.710 --> 38:20.800
If you don't have the aesthetic sense,

38:20.800 --> 38:22.800
the acting won't be any good either.

38:22.800 --> 38:23.960
Like those people who just auditioned.

38:23.960 --> 38:25.290
How did you even pick...

38:25.360 --> 38:26.620
Never mind. Forget it.

38:28.070 --> 38:29.450
Just relax and act.

38:29.800 --> 38:30.400
Good luck.

38:30.800 --> 38:31.170
Okay.

38:31.510 --> 38:32.520
I'm ready.

38:33.590 --> 38:34.600
Let's begin.

38:38.840 --> 38:39.690
How did you know

38:39.690 --> 38:40.630
that I'm Xu Shengli?

38:40.630 --> 38:41.510
With that look of yours—

38:41.510 --> 38:42.730
like a country bumpkin fresh to the city.

38:42.730 --> 38:43.610
If I couldn't tell,

38:43.610 --> 38:45.430
I'd be a terrible Production Manager.

38:45.430 --> 38:46.760
So you're Director Xue?

38:47.440 --> 38:49.370
-You’re amazing.
-Hello, Mr. Xue.

38:50.780 --> 38:52.190
You've never done this before, right?

38:52.190 --> 38:53.130
It's my first time.

38:53.130 --> 38:54.190
Oh my goodness.

38:54.880 --> 38:56.070
We're doing test shoots these days,

38:56.070 --> 38:57.300
and the filming is about to start.

38:57.300 --> 38:59.330
There's no time to train a rookie.

38:59.570 --> 39:01.300
Director Weng is just too kind.

39:01.590 --> 39:01.990
I mean,

39:02.530 --> 39:04.000
why are you causing

39:04.000 --> 39:06.000
Director Weng trouble? Seriously.

39:06.530 --> 39:08.010
Sir, I'm sorry for the trouble.

39:08.010 --> 39:09.010
But I'm a fast learner.

39:09.010 --> 39:11.030
I'll try my best not to make mistakes.

39:11.030 --> 39:13.030
You'd better not make any mistakes.

39:13.050 --> 39:14.250
If you do, you're out.

39:15.840 --> 39:17.500
And I'll still get my job done.

39:19.360 --> 39:20.210
How about this?

39:20.210 --> 39:22.470
You'll start as a production assistant.

39:23.010 --> 39:24.000
Production assistant.

39:24.000 --> 39:25.130
Have you heard of it?

39:25.390 --> 39:26.530
I know a little about it.

39:26.530 --> 39:27.400
It means doing a bit of everything,

39:27.400 --> 39:28.930
going wherever I'm needed.

39:29.050 --> 39:29.580
Exactly.

39:30.000 --> 39:31.330
It seems like you get it.

39:32.150 --> 39:33.010
Let me tell you,

39:33.880 --> 39:34.610
even PAs

39:34.650 --> 39:35.910
have specific duties.

39:36.440 --> 39:38.030
I heard you used to be a screenwriter.

39:38.030 --> 39:39.380
Yes, I'm a screenwriter.

39:39.380 --> 39:39.710
Okay.

39:40.090 --> 39:40.860
Our assistant director department

39:40.860 --> 39:41.630
happens to need someone

39:41.630 --> 39:42.530
to help actors

39:42.530 --> 39:44.330
organize their audition clips.

39:44.440 --> 39:44.800
Here's the deal.

39:44.800 --> 39:45.670
Later, go to

39:45.670 --> 39:46.760
the second-floor office

39:46.760 --> 39:47.490
and find San.

39:48.230 --> 39:48.590
Okay.

39:49.300 --> 39:49.920
Director,

39:50.030 --> 39:51.070
where will I be staying?

39:51.070 --> 39:52.880
I'd like to drop off my luggage first.

39:52.880 --> 39:53.820
The beds in this crew

39:53.820 --> 39:54.340
are only for staff

39:54.340 --> 39:55.880
with official roles.

39:56.510 --> 39:58.460
You're not on the official payroll yet.

39:58.460 --> 39:59.730
You're just an intern.

39:59.820 --> 40:01.080
There's no bed for you.

40:01.860 --> 40:02.660
Tell you what.

40:03.050 --> 40:03.860
Every morning at 6,

40:03.860 --> 40:05.030
show up at the second-floor office,

40:05.030 --> 40:06.160
and report for duty.

40:06.500 --> 40:06.880
Okay.

40:07.130 --> 40:08.530
Xu Shengli, listen to me.

40:09.300 --> 40:11.010
From now on, no matter where you are,

40:11.010 --> 40:12.070
if someone shouts "PA,"

40:12.070 --> 40:13.000
you must answer.

40:13.840 --> 40:14.960
Whether it's your job or not,

40:14.960 --> 40:16.090
it becomes your job.

40:17.150 --> 40:17.760
Filming is

40:17.760 --> 40:19.050
for the creative department.

40:19.050 --> 40:20.300
As a PA in the production team,

40:20.300 --> 40:21.350
you must be

40:21.380 --> 40:22.210
at everyone's beck and call,

40:22.210 --> 40:23.010
and stay available 24/7.

40:23.010 --> 40:23.670
No problem.

40:23.980 --> 40:24.510
Go ahead.

40:24.960 --> 40:25.380
Okay.

40:26.070 --> 40:27.270
Thank you, Director.

40:30.360 --> 40:30.920
PA.

40:32.710 --> 40:33.400
PA!

40:34.210 --> 40:34.630
Here!

40:36.000 --> 40:38.320
Mom, I passed the audition.

40:38.690 --> 40:39.480
Once filming starts,

40:39.480 --> 40:41.210
I'll be moving in with the crew.

40:41.350 --> 40:42.800
I'll definitely do my best

40:42.800 --> 40:43.800
to play this role.

40:44.420 --> 40:45.650
Also, I'll get paid this time.

40:44.890 --> 40:49.290
[Room Rates Standard]

40:47.150 --> 40:47.530
Okay.

40:47.900 --> 40:48.480
See you.

40:50.630 --> 40:52.430
How much will you earn this time?

40:53.280 --> 40:55.740
Don't worry. I'll have enough for your rent.

40:56.630 --> 40:57.670
So, after you're done filming,

40:57.670 --> 40:59.870
will you come back and stay at my hostel?

41:01.650 --> 41:03.210
That was a silly question.

41:03.510 --> 41:05.000
You'll be a big star by then.

41:05.000 --> 41:05.670
It's normal

41:05.670 --> 41:06.920
that you won't come back

41:06.920 --> 41:07.820
to this tiny place.

41:07.820 --> 41:08.710
I understand.

41:09.130 --> 41:10.510
I'm not exactly

41:10.510 --> 41:11.650
a big star yet.

41:12.340 --> 41:13.800
Well, since you said that,

41:14.150 --> 41:16.590
you're always welcome here
at Seasons Change Hostel.

41:16.590 --> 41:17.950
I'll miss you guys too.

41:18.630 --> 41:19.530
Hearing that

41:19.530 --> 41:20.800
is just so touching for me.

41:20.800 --> 41:21.960
I'm about to cry.

41:22.090 --> 41:24.680
[Registration Room]

41:23.300 --> 41:24.830
Go ahead. Let's see you cry.

41:25.320 --> 41:26.780
I can't do crying scenes.

41:26.780 --> 41:27.920
I need to learn from you.

41:27.920 --> 41:29.350
You're the actress here.

41:30.190 --> 41:30.960
Enough.

41:31.510 --> 41:32.670
I'll go buy something good to eat.

41:32.670 --> 41:34.000
Let's grab a bite later.

41:34.340 --> 41:34.770
Sure.

41:34.800 --> 41:35.650
Leave the rest to me.

41:35.650 --> 41:37.300
I'll get everything sorted out perfectly.

41:37.300 --> 41:37.720
Great.

41:46.190 --> 41:47.590
Here comes the main dish.

41:47.920 --> 41:49.710
Come on.

41:50.170 --> 41:52.300
-It smells good.
-Thank you, Zongbao.

41:52.400 --> 41:53.600
Come on, dig in.

41:53.900 --> 41:55.230
This is a real feast today.

41:55.230 --> 41:56.350
Eat up, everyone.

41:56.460 --> 41:57.320
Have some more.

41:58.490 --> 41:59.210
As usual,

42:00.010 --> 42:01.470
I'll say a few words first.

42:02.150 --> 42:02.960
Today,

42:03.090 --> 42:05.210
Ranran is the main character here.

42:05.300 --> 42:05.900
Am I right?

42:06.210 --> 42:08.010
According to He'nan tradition,

42:08.380 --> 42:08.980
I'll begin

42:09.010 --> 42:10.440
with a toast.

42:12.260 --> 42:13.460
Cheers. Have a drink.

42:14.800 --> 42:16.340
For Ranran,

42:16.520 --> 42:19.580
-her hard work has finally paid off.
-Don't drink it up.

42:19.610 --> 42:20.760
As the old saying goes,

42:20.760 --> 42:23.050
the first step is always the hardest.

42:23.710 --> 42:24.570
And you've made a great start.

42:24.570 --> 42:25.940
Great!

42:25.940 --> 42:27.840
Here. The second cup.

42:27.840 --> 42:28.550
You hold it.

42:28.570 --> 42:29.590
Just hold it.

42:29.730 --> 42:30.920
The second cup is called

42:30.920 --> 42:31.960
"Holding the Cup."

42:31.960 --> 42:32.550
Holding the Cup.

42:32.550 --> 42:33.230
Holding the Cup.

42:33.230 --> 42:35.250
Alright, alright.

42:35.550 --> 42:36.320
For the second toast,

42:36.320 --> 42:38.570
Ranran is a supporting actress now,

42:38.980 --> 42:42.440
but tomorrow she'll be
the second lead or even the female lead.

42:42.760 --> 42:43.220
Come on.

42:43.550 --> 42:44.920
For the third cup,

42:45.130 --> 42:46.460
it's called a "top-up."

42:47.280 --> 42:47.860
Just take a sip.

42:47.860 --> 42:48.900
Alright, that's enough.

42:48.900 --> 42:49.590
Ranran,

42:49.960 --> 42:52.420
becoming Superstar Shen

42:53.170 --> 42:54.630
is just around the corner!

42:54.690 --> 42:55.610
Great.

42:55.630 --> 42:56.230
Well said!

42:56.570 --> 42:57.070
Great.
